I'm trying to create plugin with variant  for Hebrew language.
I use language key with variant in atlassian-plugin.xml, like this:
{code}
    <language name="Hebrew (Israel) (MyCompany)" key="iw_IL_MyCompany" language="iw" country="IL">
    </language>
{code}
But it don't works, don't load my language file {{/src/main/resources/com/atlassian/jira/web/action/JiraWebActionSupport_iw_IL_MyCompany.properties}} and show me English (the key="iw_IL" is work).
Looks like the problem in the method {{com.atlassian.jira.util.LocaleParser#computeLocale()}}

It has only two options for locale: by language and language+country, but there are no option for language+country+variant:
{code}
            locale = new Locale(localeString.substring(0, _pos), localeString.substring(_pos + 1));
{code}
and
{code}
           locale = new Locale(localeString);
{code}

